name: setPotionDurationMax
desc: Toggle the isPotionDurationMax field.

name: isKeyDown
desc: Returns whether the specified key binding is currently being pressed.

name: saveExtraData
desc: Save extra data not associated with any Chunk.  Not saved during autosave, only during world unload.  Currently unimplemented.

name: saveChunkData
desc: saves chunk data - currently only called during execution of the Save All command

name: onBroken
desc: Called when this entity is broken. Entity parameter may be null.

name: removeFrameFromMap
desc: Removes the dot representing this frame's position from the map when the item frame is broken.

name: setCustomName
desc: Sets the name of this inventory. This is displayed to the client on opening.

name: dismountEntity
desc: Moves the entity to a position out of the way of its mount.

name: updateLeashedState
desc: Applies logic related to leashes, for example dragging the entity or breaking the leash.

name: clearLeashed
desc: Removes the leash from this entity. Second parameter tells whether to send a packet to surrounding players.

name: setLeashedToEntity
desc: Sets the entity to be leashed to.

name: enablePersistence
desc: Enable the Entity persistence

name: hasHome
desc: Returns whether a home area is defined for this entity.

name: addGrowth
desc: "Adds the value of the parameter times 20 to the age of this entity. If the entity is an adult (if the entity's age is greater than 0), it will have no effect."

name: canMate
desc: Return true if the horse entity ready to mate. (no rider, not riding, tame, adult, not steril...)

name: spawnHorseParticles
desc: "Spawns particles for the horse entity. par1 tells whether to spawn hearts. If it is false, it spawns smoke."

name: isSterile
desc: Return true if the horse entity is sterile (Undead || Mule)

name: canCarryChest
desc: Return true if the horse entity can carry a chest.

name: isUndead
desc: Used to know if the horse can be leashed, if he can mate, or if we can interact with him

name: canWearArmor
desc: Return true if the horse entity can wear an armor

name: getHorseArmorIndex
desc: 0 = iron, 1 = gold, 2 = diamond

name: getHorseType
desc: Returns the horse type. 0 = Normal, 1 = Donkey, 2 = Mule, 3 = Undead Horse, 4 = Skeleton Horse

name: verifySellingItem
desc: Notifies the merchant of a possible merchantrecipe being fulfilled or not. Usually, this is just a sound byte being played depending if the suggested itemstack is not null.

name: getLocationSkin
desc: Returns true if the player instance has an associated skin.

name: getLocationSkin
desc: Returns true if the username has an associated skin.\n \n@param username The username of the player being checked.

name: getSectionName
desc: The name of this section type as it appears in JSON.

name: getGson
desc: Returns a Gson instance with type adapters registered for metadata sections.

name: getTextWithoutFormattingCodes
desc: Returns a copy of the given string, with formatting codes stripped away.\n \n@param text The text to strip formatting codes from

name: setBoxRotation
desc: Sets the rotations for a ModelRenderer in the ModelHorse class.

name: updateHorseRotation
desc: Fixes and offsets a rotation in the ModelHorse class.

name: isRidingHorse
desc: Checks if the player is riding a horse, used to chose the GUI to open

name: getEntityTexture
desc: Returns the location of an entity's texture. Doesn't seem to be called unless you call Render.bindEntityTexture.

name: canRenderName
desc: Test if the entity name must be rendered

name: interpolateValue
desc: Gets the value between start and end according to pct

name: getOriginY
desc: Returns the Y position of this icon on its texture sheet, in pixels.

name: getAttribute
desc: Get the Attribute this is an instance of

name: getModifier
desc: Returns attribute modifier, if any, by the given UUID

name: registerAttribute
desc: Registers an attribute with this AttributeMap, returns a modifiable AttributeInstance associated with this map

name: isSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: setSaved
desc: @see #isSaved

name: registerPotionAttributeModifier
desc: Used by potions to register the attribute they modify.

name: sendMetadataToAllAssociatedPlayers
desc: Sends the entity metadata (DataWatcher) and attributes to all players tracking this entity, including the entity itself if a player.

name: processChunk
desc: This method currently only increases chunk inhabited time. Extension is possible in next versions

name: increaseInhabitedTime
desc: Increases chunk inhabited time every 8000 ticks

name: getItemAttributeModifiers
desc: Gets a map of item attribute modifiers, used by ItemSword to increase hit damage.

name: getByNameOrId
desc: Tries to get an Item by it's name (e.g. minecraft:apple) or a String representation of a numerical ID. If both fail, null is returned.

name: itemInteractionForEntity
desc: Returns true if the item can be used on the given entity, e.g. shears on sheep.

name: getRelevantEnchantmentTypes
desc: Returns the enchantment types relevant to this tab

name: setRelevantEnchantmentTypes
desc: Sets the enchantment types for populating this tab with enchanting books

name: canBeHovered
desc: Actualy only call when we want to render the white square effect over the slots. Return always True, except for the armor slot of the Donkey/Mule (we can't interact with the Undead and Skeleton horses)

name: writeBaseAttributeMapToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagList from a BaseAttributeMap, including all its AttributeInstances

name: readAttributeModifierFromNBT
desc: Creates an AttributeModifier from an NBTTagCompound

name: writeAttributeInstanceToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagCompound from an AttributeInstance, including its AttributeModifiers

name: writeAttributeModifierToNBT
desc: Creates an NBTTagCompound from an AttributeModifier

name: getPathSearchRange
desc: Gets the maximum distance that the path finding will search in.

name: getAttributeModifiers
desc: Gets the attribute modifiers for this ItemStack.\nWill check for an NBT tag list containing modifiers for the stack.

name: createServerGui
desc: Creates the server GUI and sets it visible for the user.

name: getStatsComponent
desc: Generates new StatsComponent and returns it.

name: getPlayerListComponent
desc: Generates new PlayerListComponent and returns it.

name: getCurrentMoonPhaseFactor
desc: gets the current fullness of the moon expressed as a float between 1.0 and 0.0, in steps of .25

name: interactFirst
desc: First layer of player interaction

name: getOriginX
desc: Returns the X position of this icon on its texture sheet, in pixels.

name: getMinecraftStartTimeMillis
desc: Returns the saved value of System#currentTimeMillis when the game started

name: loadLocaleDataFiles
desc: par2 is a list of languages. For each language $L and domain $D, attempts to load the resource $D:lang/$L.lang

name: formatMessage
desc: Calls String.format(translateKey(key), params)

name: translateKeyPrivate
desc: Returns the translation, or the key itself if the key could not be translated.

name: loadLocaleData
desc: par1 is a list of Resources

name: format
desc: format(a, b) is equivalent to String.format(translate(a), b). Args: translationKey, params...

name: replaceWith
desc: Replaces all the current instance's translations with the ones that are passed in.

name: tryTranslateKey
desc: Tries to look up a translation for the given key; spits back the key if no result was found.

name: clearCustomName
desc: Clear any custom name set for this ItemStack

name: isOnTeam
desc: Returns true if the entity is on a specific team.

name: isSameTeam
desc: Same as ==

name: readStructureFromNBT
desc: (abstract) Helper method to read subclass data from NBT

name: writeStructureToNBT
desc: (abstract) Helper method to write subclass data to NBT

name: addChatMessage
desc: Notifies this sender of some sort of information.  This is for messages intended to display to the user.  Used for typical output (like "you asked for whether or not this game rule is set, so here's your answer"), warnings (like "I fetched this block for you by ID, but I'd like you to know that every time you do this, I die a little inside"), and errors (like "it's not called iron_pixacke, silly").

name: getLastOutput
desc: Returns the lastOutput.

name: setCommand
desc: Sets the command.

name: getCustomName
desc: Returns the customName of the command block.

name: writeDataToNBT
desc: Stores data to NBT format.

name: readDataFromNBT
desc: Reads NBT formatting and stored data into variables.

name: getSuccessCount
desc: returns the successCount int.

name: doesEntityNotTriggerPressurePlate
desc: Return whether this entity should NOT trigger a pressure plate or a tripwire.

name: hasCustomName
desc: Returns true if this thing is named

name: addMapping
desc: Adds a new two-way mapping between the class and its string name in both hashmaps.

name: createAndLoadEntity
desc: Creates a new entity and loads its data from the specified NBT.

name: validate
desc: validates a tile entity

name: hasWorldObj
desc: Returns true if the worldObj isn't null.

name: getWorld
desc: Returns the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: setWorldObj
desc: Sets the worldObj for this tileEntity.

name: getDistanceSq
desc: Returns the square of the distance between this entity and the passed in coordinates.

name: getBlockType
desc: Gets the block type at the location of this entity (client-only).

name: invalidate
desc: invalidates a tile entity

name: getDescriptionPacket
desc: Allows for a specialized description packet to be created. This is often used to sync tile entity data from the server to the client easily. For example this is used by signs to synchronise the text to be displayed.

name: clearPistonTileEntity
desc: removes a piston's tile entity (and if the piston is moving, stops it)

name: isExtending
desc: Returns true if a piston is extending

name: changePitch
desc: change pitch by -> (currentPitch + 1) % 25

name: setEditable
desc: Sets the sign's isEditable flag to the specified parameter.

name: canSmelt
desc: Returns true if the furnace can smelt an item, i.e. has a source item, destination stack isn't full, etc.

name: smeltItem
desc: Turn one item from the furnace source stack into the appropriate smelted item in the furnace result stack

name: isBurning
desc: Furnace isBurning

name: getItemBurnTime
desc: Returns the number of ticks that the supplied fuel item will keep the furnace burning, or 0 if the item isn't fuel

name: checkForAdjacentChests
desc: Performs the check for adjacent chests to determine if this chest is double or not.

name: addItemStack
desc: Add the given ItemStack to this Dispenser. Return the Slot the Item was placed in or -1 if no free slot is available.

name: consumeInventoryItem
desc: removed one item of specified Item from inventory (if it is in a stack, the stack size will reduce with 1)

name: hasItem
desc: Checks if a specified Item is inside the inventory

name: multiplySize
desc: Multiplies the height and width by the provided float.\n \n@param size The size to multiply the height and width of the entity by.

name: setChildSize
desc: sets the size of the entity to be half of its current size if true.\n \n@param isChild If the mob is a child it's height and width will be halved. Otherwise the size will remain the same.

name: explode
desc: Creates an explosion as determined by this creeper's power and explosion radius.

name: setHorseArmorStack
desc: Set horse armor stack (for example: new ItemStack(Items.iron_horse_armor))

name: getUUID
desc: Gets a players UUID given their GameProfie

name: canHarvestBlock
desc: Checks if the player has the ability to harvest a block (checks current inventory item for a tool if necessary)

name: getGameProfile
desc: Returns the GameProfile for this player

name: drawModalRectWithCustomSizedTexture
desc: Draws a textured rectangle at z = 0. Args: x, y, u, v, width, height, textureWidth, textureHeight

name: drawButton
desc: Draws this button to the screen.

name: getHoverState
desc: Returns 0 if the button is disabled, 1 if the mouse is NOT hovering over this button and 2 if it IS hovering over this button.

name: isMouseOver
desc: Whether the mouse cursor is currently over the button.

name: mousePressed
desc: Returns true if the mouse has been pressed on this control. Equivalent of MouseListener.mousePressed(MouseEvent e).

name: mouseReleased
desc: Fired when the mouse button is released. Equivalent of MouseListener.mouseReleased(MouseEvent e).

name: mouseDragged
desc: Fired when the mouse button is dragged. Equivalent of MouseListener.mouseDragged(MouseEvent e).

name: getChatGUI
desc: returns a pointer to the persistant Chat GUI, containing all previous chat messages and such

name: deleteFromCursor
desc: delete the selected text, otherwsie deletes characters from either side of the cursor. params: delete num

name: getVisible
desc: returns true if this textbox is visible

name: deleteWords
desc: Deletes the specified number of words starting at the cursor position. Negative numbers will delete words left of the cursor.

name: updateCursorCounter
desc: Increments the cursor counter

name: getText
desc: Returns the contents of the textbox

name: setText
desc: Sets the text of the textbox

name: getEnableBackgroundDrawing
desc: get enable drawing background and outline

name: moveCursorBy
desc: Moves the text cursor by a specified number of characters and clears the selection

name: getNthWordFromPos
desc: gets the position of the nth word. N may be negative, then it looks backwards. params: N, position

name: setEnableBackgroundDrawing
desc: enable drawing background and outline

name: getSelectionEnd
desc: the side of the selection that is not the cursor, may be the same as the cursor

name: getNthWordFromCursor
desc: see @getNthNextWordFromPos() params: N, position

name: drawCursorVertical
desc: draws the vertical line cursor in the textbox

name: setVisible
desc: Sets whether or not this textbox is visible

name: setCursorPosition
desc: sets the position of the cursor to the provided index

name: writeText
desc: replaces selected text, or inserts text at the position on the cursor

name: mouseClicked
desc: Args: x, y, buttonClicked

name: setTextColor
desc: Sets the text colour for this textbox (disabled text will not use this colour)

name: drawTextBox
desc: Draws the textbox

name: setFocused
desc: Sets focus to this gui element

name: setCursorPositionZero
desc: sets the cursors position to the beginning

name: getCursorPosition
desc: returns the current position of the cursor

name: setSelectionPos
desc: Sets the position of the selection anchor (i.e. position the selection was started at)

name: getWidth
desc: returns the width of the textbox depending on if background drawing is enabled

name: textboxKeyTyped
desc: Call this method from your GuiScreen to process the keys into the textbox

name: setCursorPositionEnd
desc: sets the cursors position to after the text

name: setCanLoseFocus
desc: if true the textbox can lose focus by clicking elsewhere on the screen

name: isFocused
desc: Getter for the focused field

name: getSelectedText
desc: returns the text between the cursor and selectionEnd

name: getMaxStringLength
desc: returns the maximum number of character that can be contained in this textbox

name: scroll
desc: Scrolls the chat by the given number of lines.

name: clearChatMessages
desc: Clears the chat.

name: printChatMessageWithOptionalDeletion
desc: prints the ChatComponent to Chat. If the ID is not 0, deletes an existing Chat Line of that ID from the GUI

name: getChatComponent
desc: Gets the chat component under the mouse

name: getSentMessages
desc: Gets the list of messages previously sent through the chat GUI

name: addToSentMessages
desc: Adds this string to the list of sent messages, for recall using the up/down arrow keys

name: resetScroll
desc: Resets the chat scroll (executed when the GUI is closed, among others)

name: getChatOpen
desc: Returns true if the chat GUI is open

name: deleteChatLine
desc: finds and deletes a Chat line by ID

name: getChatScale
desc: Returns the chatscale from mc.gameSettings.chatScale

name: handleInput
desc: Delegates mouse and keyboard input.

name: isCtrlKeyDown
desc: Returns true if either windows ctrl key is down or if either mac meta key is down

name: isShiftKeyDown
desc: Returns true if either shift key is down

name: mouseClickMove
desc: Called when a mouse button is pressed and the mouse is moved around. Parameters are : mouseX, mouseY, lastButtonClicked & timeSinceMouseClick.

name: handleMouseInput
desc: Handles mouse input.

name: setClipboardString
desc: Stores the given string in the system clipboard

name: drawDefaultBackground
desc: Draws either a gradient over the background screen (when it exists) or a flat gradient over background.png

name: getClipboardString
desc: Returns a string stored in the system clipboard.

name: drawBackground
desc: Draws the background (i is always 0 as of 1.2.2)

name: drawCreativeTabHoveringText
desc: Draws the text when mouse is over creative inventory tab. Params: current creative tab to be checked, current mouse x position, current mouse y position.

name: setWorldAndResolution
desc: Causes the screen to lay out its subcomponents again. This is the equivalent of the Java call Container.validate()

name: onGuiClosed
desc: Called when the screen is unloaded. Used to disable keyboard repeat events

name: handleKeyboardInput
desc: Handles keyboard input.

name: mouseReleased
desc: Called when a mouse button is released.  Args : mouseX, mouseY, releaseButton

name: setButtonDelay
desc: Sets the number of ticks to wait before enabling the buttons.

name: copyLinkToClipboard
desc: Copies the link to the system clipboard.

name: getSentHistory
desc: input is relative and is applied directly to the sentHistoryCursor so -1 is the previous message, 1 is the next message from the current cursor position\n \n@param msgPos The position of the message in the sent chat history relative to the current message.

name: pageGetCurrent
desc: Returns the entire text of the current page as determined by currPage

name: pageSetCurrent
desc: Sets the text of the current page as determined by currPage

name: pageInsertIntoCurrent
desc: Processes any text getting inserted into the current page, enforcing the page size limit

name: keyTypedInTitle
desc: Processes keystrokes when editing the title of a book

name: keyTypedInBook
desc: Processes keystrokes when editing the text of a book

name: drawSprite
desc: Draws a sprite from assets/textures/gui/container/stats_icons.png

name: drawButtonBackground
desc: Draws a gray box that serves as a button background.

name: getSlotAtPosition
desc: Returns the slot at the given coordinates or null if there is none.

name: drawGuiContainerBackgroundLayer
desc: Args : renderPartialTicks, mouseX, mouseY

name: isPointInRegion
desc: Test if the 2D point is in a rectangle (relative to the GUI). Args : rectX, rectY, rectWidth, rectHeight, pointX, pointY

name: drawGuiContainerForegroundLayer
desc: Draw the foreground layer for the GuiContainer (everything in front of the items). Args : mouseX, mouseY

name: isMouseOverSlot
desc: Returns if the passed mouse position is over the specified slot. Args : slot, mouseX, mouseY

name: drawItemStack
desc: Render an ItemStack. Args : stack, x, y, format

name: checkHotbarKeys
desc: This function is what controls the hotbar shortcut check when you press a number key when hovering a stack. Args : keyCode, Returns true if a Hotbar key is pressed, else false

name: handleMouseClick
desc: Called when the mouse is clicked over a slot or outside the gui.

name: drawActivePotionEffects
desc: Display the potion effects list

name: drawEntityOnScreen
desc: Draws the entity to the screen. Args: xPos, yPos, scale, mouseX, mouseY, entityLiving

name: renderCreativeInventoryHoveringText
desc: Renders the creative inventory hovering text if mouse is over it. Returns true if did render or false otherwise. Params: current creative tab to be checked, current mouse x position, current mouse y position.

name: needsScrollBars
desc: returns (if you are not on the inventoryTab) and (the flag isn't set) and (you have more than 1 page of items)

name: updateBiomesExplored
desc: Updates all biomes that have been explored by this player and triggers Adventuring Time if player qualifies.

name: getStatFile
desc: Gets the stats file for reading achievements

name: displayGuiScreen
desc: Sets the argument GuiScreen as the main (topmost visible) screen.

name: middleClickMouse
desc: Called when user clicked he's mouse middle button (pick block)

name: rightClickMouse
desc: Called when user clicked he's mouse right button (place)

name: getDifficulty
desc: Get the server's difficulty

name: saveToFile
desc: Saves this CrashReport to the given file and returns a value indicating whether we were successful at doing so.

name: getItemByText
desc: Gets the Item specified by the given text string.  First checks the item registry, then tries by parsing the string as an integer ID (deprecated).  Warns the sender if we matched by parsing the ID.  Throws if the item wasn't found.  Returns the item if it was found.

name: getBlockByText
desc: Gets the Block specified by the given text string.  First checks the block registry, then tries by parsing the string as an integer ID (deprecated).  Warns the sender if we matched by parsing the ID.  Throws if the block wasn't found.  Returns the block if it was found.

name: onDisconnect
desc: Invoked when disconnecting, the parameter is a ChatComponent describing the reason for termination

name: handleBlockChange
desc: Updates the block and metadata and generates a blockupdate (and notify the clients)

name: handleSpawnObject
desc: Spawns an instance of the objecttype indicated by the packet and sets its position and momentum

name: handleEntityStatus
desc: Invokes the entities' handleUpdateHealth method which is implemented in LivingBase (hurt/death), MinecartMobSpawner (spawn delay), FireworkRocket & MinecartTNT (explosion), IronGolem (throwing,...), Witch (spawn particles), Zombie (villager transformation), Animal (breeding mode particles), Horse (breeding/smoke particles), Sheep (...), Tameable (...), Villager (particles for breeding mode, angry and happy), Wolf (...)

name: handleSpawnPlayer
desc: Handles the creation of a nearby player entity, sets the position and held item

name: handleDestroyEntities
desc: Locally eliminates the entities. Invoked by the server when the items are in fact destroyed, or the player is no longer registered as required to monitor them. The latter  happens when distance between the player and item increases beyond a certain treshold (typically the viewing distance)

name: handleConfirmTransaction
desc: Verifies that the server and client are synchronized with respect to the inventory/container opened by the player and confirms if it is the case.

name: handleCustomPayload
desc: Handles packets that have room for a channel specification. Vanilla implemented channels are "MC|TrList" to acquire a MerchantRecipeList trades for a villager merchant, "MC|Brand" which sets the server brand? on the player instance and finally "MC|RPack" which the server uses to communicate the identifier of the default server resourcepack for the client to load.

name: handleWindowItems
desc: Handles the placement of a specified ItemStack in a specified container/inventory slot

name: handleEntityVelocity
desc: Sets the velocity of the specified entity to the specified value

name: handleWindowProperty
desc: Sets the progressbar of the opened window to the specified value

name: handleTeams
desc: Updates a team managed by the scoreboard: Create/Remove the team registration, Register/Remove the player-team-memberships, Set team displayname/prefix/suffix and/or whether friendly fire is enabled

name: handleUpdateSign
desc: Updates a specified sign with the specified text lines

name: handleUpdateScore
desc: Either updates the score with a specified value or removes the score for an objective

name: handleChat
desc: Prints a chatmessage in the chat GUI

name: handleDisconnect
desc: Closes the network channel

name: handleDisplayScoreboard
desc: Removes or sets the ScoreObjective to be displayed at a particular scoreboard position (list, sidebar, below name)

name: handleHeldItemChange
desc: Updates which hotbar slot of the player is currently selected

name: handlePlayerPosLook
desc: Handles changes in player positioning and rotation such as when travelling to a new dimension, (re)spawning, mounting horses etc. Seems to immediately reply to the server with the clients post-processing perspective on the player positioning

name: handleEntityMovement
desc: Updates the specified entity's position by the specified relative moment and absolute rotation. Note that subclassing of the packet allows for the specification of a subset of this data (e.g. only rel. position, abs. rotation or both).

name: handleBlockAction
desc: Triggers Block.onBlockEventReceived, which is implemented in BlockPistonBase for extension/retraction, BlockNote for setting the instrument (including audiovisual feedback) and in BlockContainer to set the number of players accessing a (Ender)Chest

name: handleChunkData
desc: Updates the specified chunk with the supplied data, marks it for re-rendering and lighting recalculation

name: handleMaps
desc: Updates the worlds MapStorage with the specified MapData for the specified map-identifier and invokes a MapItemRenderer for it

name: handleOpenWindow
desc: Displays a GUI by ID. In order starting from id 0: Chest, Workbench, Furnace, Dispenser, Enchanting table, Brewing stand, Villager merchant, Beacon, Anvil, Hopper, Dropper, Horse

name: handleSetSlot
desc: Handles pickin up an ItemStack or dropping one in your inventory or an open (non-creative) container

name: handleEntityHeadLook
desc: Updates the direction in which the specified entity is looking, normally this head rotation is independent of the rotation of the entity itself

name: handleSignEditorOpen
desc: Creates a sign in the specified location if it didn't exist and opens the GUI to edit its text

name: handleUpdateTileEntity
desc: Updates the NBTTagCompound metadata of instances of the following entitytypes: Mob spawners, command blocks, beacons, skulls, flowerpot

name: handleTabComplete
desc: Displays the available command-completion options the server knows of

name: handleEntityTeleport
desc: Updates an entity's position and rotation as specified by the packet

name: handleCloseWindow
desc: Resets the ItemStack held in hand and closes the window that is opened

name: handleUseBed
desc: Retrieves the player identified by the packet, puts him to sleep if possible (and flags whether all players are asleep)

name: handleAnimation
desc: Renders a specified animation: Waking up a player, a living entity swinging its currently held item, being hurt or receiving a critical hit by normal or magical means

name: handleSpawnMob
desc: Spawns the mob entity at the specified location, with the specified rotation, momentum and type. Updates the entities Datawatchers with the entity metadata specified in the packet

name: handleJoinGame
desc: Registers some server properties (gametype,hardcore-mode,terraintype,difficulty,player limit), creates a new WorldClient and sets the player initial dimension

name: handleExplosion
desc: Initiates a new explosion (sound, particles, drop spawn) for the affected blocks indicated by the packet.

name: handleEntityMetadata
desc: Invoked when the server registers new proximate objects in your watchlist or when objects in your watchlist have changed -> Registers any changes locally

name: handleSpawnExperienceOrb
desc: Spawns an experience orb and sets its value (amount of XP)

name: handleMultiBlockChange
desc: Received from the servers PlayerManager if between 1 and 64 blocks in a chunk are changed. If only one block requires an update, the server sends S23PacketBlockChange and if 64 or more blocks are changed, the server sends S21PacketChunkData

name: handleSpawnPainting
desc: Handles the spawning of a painting object

name: handleParticles
desc: Spawns a specified number of particles at the specified location with a randomized displacement according to specified bounds

name: handleEntityProperties
desc: Updates en entity's attributes and their respective modifiers, which are used for speed bonusses (player sprinting, animals fleeing, baby speed), weapon/tool attackDamage, hostiles followRange randomization, zombie maxHealth and knockback resistance as well as reinforcement spawning chance.

name: handleScoreboardObjective
desc: May create a scoreboard objective, remove an objective from the scoreboard or update an objectives' displayname

name: handleSpawnGlobalEntity
desc: Handles globally visible entities. Used in vanilla for lightning bolts

name: handleStatistics
desc: Updates the players statistics or achievements

name: handleBlockBreakAnim
desc: Updates all registered IWorldAccess instances with destroyBlockInWorldPartially

name: cleanup
desc: Clears the WorldClient instance associated with this NetHandlerPlayClient

name: getNetworkManager
desc: Returns this the NetworkManager instance registered with this NetworkHandlerPlayClient

name: processEnchantItem
desc: Enchants the item identified by the packet given some convoluted conditions (matching window, which should/shouldn't be in use?)

name: processConfirmTransaction
desc: Received in response to the server requesting to confirm that the client-side open container matches the servers' after a mismatched container-slot manipulation. It will unlock the player's ability to manipulate the container contents

name: processUseEntity
desc: Processes interactions ((un)leashing, opening command block GUI) and attacks on an entity with players currently equipped item

name: processTabComplete
desc: Retrieves possible tab completions for the requested command string and sends them to the client

name: processClientStatus
desc: Processes the client status updates: respawn attempt from player, opening statistics or achievements, or acquiring 'open inventory' achievement

name: processCreativeInventoryAction
desc: Update the server with an ItemStack in a slot.

name: processPlayerDigging
desc: Processes the player initiating/stopping digging on a particular spot, as well as a player dropping items?. (0: initiated, 1: reinitiated, 2? , 3-4 drop item (respectively without or with player control), 5: stopped; x,y,z, side clicked on;)

name: processPlayerBlockPlacement
desc: Processes block placement and block activation (anvil, furnace, etc.)

name: processPlayer
desc: Processes clients perspective on player positioning and/or orientation

name: processPlayerAbilities
desc: Processes a player starting/stopping flying

name: processVanilla250Packet
desc: Synchronizes serverside and clientside book contents and signing

name: processClickWindow

name: writeVarIntToBuffer
desc: Writes a compressed int to the buffer. The smallest number of bytes to fit the passed int will be written. Of each such byte only 7 bits will be used to describe the actual value since its most significant bit dictates whether the next byte is part of that same int. Micro-optimization for int values that are expected to have values below 128.
